title: Cnut the Great
summary: Cnut the Great (/kəˈnjuːt/;[2] Old English: Cnut cyning; Old Norse: Knútr inn ríki [ˈknuːtr ˈinː ˈriːke];[lower-alpha 1] died 12 November 1035), also known as Canute, was King of England, Denmark and Norway, often referred to together as the North Sea Empire during his rule.
